# Supermicro BMC Patterns

## Account Management

- AccountTypes field: GPU chassis support `["IPMI", "Redfish"]`, some CPU chassis only `["Redfish"]`
- When creating accounts, always try to set AccountTypes to include IPMI
- Use Manager.Reset (GracefulRestart) to restart a hung BMC
- BMC restart requires Administrator role — use an admin account, not the maas Operator account

## Power Operations

- BootSourceOverrideEnabled "Once" is consumed after one boot — MAAS sets this before each commissioning/deploy
- If PXE boot doesn't work, manually set via Redfish PATCH to Systems/1 Boot object
- ForceOn vs On: both accepted but neither guarantees the system powers on (hardware issue if BMC returns 200 but PowerState stays Off)

## Account Lockout

- Default: threshold=3, duration=30s
- Disable via PATCH to AccountService: `{"AccountLockoutThreshold": 0}`
- Some firmware versions reject threshold changes (return 400)
- Account lockout manifests as "Access denied while performing power action" in MAAS, not "incorrect password"
